title: MultiSport

creator: Benefit Systems SA
descriptionHtml:
With the MultiSport app, you can quickly find sports facilities in your area. The app works like your plastic MultiSport card and your ID in one! You can enter all facilities without showing the card or your ID at the entrance – just verify your identity in the app. If you have more than one card, you can conveniently manage all of them from the app - add, remove cards, and register visits.

What you’ll find in the application:
- Search for facilities – find sports facilities in your vicinity and create a list of favorite
locations and activities.
- Mobile card - the MultiSport application works like your card and ID in one. Add your card number, upload your photo to the application, confirm your identity at the facility, and done. With each visit, just generate a QR code and scan it to enter the facility.
- Additional cards - if you have more than one card, you can register group entries to sports facilities with the app.
- Online workouts - work out anywhere and any time you want! Bad weather? Stay home and choose a training program that best suits your needs.
- MultiSport Kids - with the MultiSport Kids or MultiSport Kids Aqua cards, your child can choose from various activities. Swimming pool, dance, martial arts, rope parks, and climbing walls are just some of them! The app gives additional access to a wide range of fairy tales read by Agnieszka Więdłocha, as well as many other activities - physical activities for children at home with MultiSport Atmosphere animators and family activities so that you can have fun together.
- Pedometer - monitor your daily physical activity and reach your goals.
- Backup QR code - even if you don't have wi-fi, you can sign up for classes and enter facilities. There is a spare QR code that's available offline.

Who is the app for
● You can download and use the application for free if you already have a physical MultiSport card.
● Most of the functionalities require an active MultiSPort account. You can set up an account at www.kartamultisport.pl;
● The application is free and available in Poland.

creator: Benefit Systems SA
descriptionHtml:
Already have a MultiSport card? Great! Download the MultiSport mobile app, which is like a card and your ID in one, and enjoy convenient access to sports facilities - no need to show your ID and the physical card. • Pedometer - monitor your daily physical activity.
• Backup QR code - register entries to facilities even when you're offline – the app has QR codes that are available without access to the internet.

Who is it for?
• For those that already have a MuliSport card and an active Multisport account.
• The application is free and available in Poland.
